// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// LoopHarness — build-time configuration
//
// Copy this file to `Secrets.xcconfig` (gitignored) before building.
// The project's base configuration already references Secrets.xcconfig,
// so no Xcode GUI step is needed — just create the file.
//
// What goes here:
//   1. DEVELOPMENT_TEAM — your 10-char Apple Developer Team ID.
//      Without this, Xcode will sign locally ("Sign to Run Locally")
//      which is fine for the simulator but not for a device build.
//      Find yours at developer.apple.com → Account → Membership, or
//      in Xcode → Settings → Accounts → your team → Team ID.
//
//   2. API keys (optional). The app reads keys from the Keychain at
//      runtime (Settings → Integrations), so these are NOT required.
//      If you'd rather bake them in at build time, set them here —
//      Info.plist `$(VAR)` entries resolve from this file. A blank or
//      `$(VAR)`-shaped value makes KeyStore fall back to the in-app
//      entry flow.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// Signing — set to your Apple Developer Team ID
DEVELOPMENT_TEAM =

// API keys — optional, prefer in-app Settings → Integrations
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY =
ELEVEN_LABS_KEY =
EXA_API_KEY =
OPENAI_API_KEY =
CURSOR_API_KEY =
OBSIDIAN_API_KEY =
OBSIDIAN_BASE_URL =
